The title race between Liverpool and Manchester City is looking set to go to the wire. We look at the figures as the two sides battle it out for the Premier League crown. City is just three points adrift of Liverpool with just three games to go to the end of the season. City lead the table with 86 points having won 27 of their 35 games, drawn in five and lost only three. They have have scored 89 goals and conceded only 21 to give them a superior goal difference of 68 goals. On the other hand, Liverpool have won 25 games, drawn in eight and lost just two. They have scored two goals less than City (87), conceded two more than City (23) to post an equally impressive goal difference of 64. Jurgen Klopps' charges are second on the league table with 83 points.